Student Name: Olorunfemi Ogunbanwo
What is GitHub, and what are its primary functions and features? Explain how it supports collaborative software development. 
Answer: GitHub is a web-based Git repository hosting service, which offers all of the distributed revision control and source code management functionality f git as well as adding its own features. It is a website that hosts git repositories on a remote server
What is a GitHub repository? Describe how to create a new repository and the essential elements that should be included in it. 
Answer: A Git repository is a storage location where our project files and the entire history of their changes are tracked
Creating a new repository involve creating a GitHub account, then inside the GitHub account, a repository will be created.
Explain the concept of version control in the context of Git. How does GitHub enhance version control for developers? 
Answer: Version control will track and save all the changes to our code base, it will allow collaboration with other developers
What are branches in GitHub, and why are they important? Describe the process of creating a branch, making changes, and merging it back into the main branch. 
Answer: Branching allow developers to collaborate on a project and later combine their work. Individual developers will be on different branches when the project is complete, then the developers will merge the branches
What is a pull request in GitHub, and how does it facilitate code reviews and collaboration? Outline the steps to create and review a pull request. 
Answer: A pull request is transferring a file from the online GitHub repository to our local machine. To make a pull request, sign in to GitHub account, open the desired project inside the vscode terminal, and use git pull command to pull the repository, 
What is Visual Studio, and what are its key features? How does it differ from Visual Studio Code?
Answer: Visual Studio is a powerful IDE suited for large-scale and enterprise-level development, offering a comprehensive set of tools and features, while Visual Studio Code is a lightweight, fast, and highly customizable code editor suitable for a wide range of development tasks
Describe the steps to integrate a GitHub repository with Visual Studio. How does this integration enhance the development workflow? 
Answer: Visual studio installation, sign in to GitHub, cone the GitHub repository, create a new project and connect to GitHub then lastly publish to GitHub.
Explain the debugging tools available in Visual Studio. How can developers use these tools to identify and fix issues in their code?
Answers: debugging tools, are used by developers to efficiently diagnose and resolve errors, leading to more robust and reliable applications
